claim.claim-text:
1. A method of processing data at a communication device that maintains a receiving window, the receiving window defining a set of information units that the communication device may accept, the method comprising:
setting up a block acknowledgement session with a transmitting station, including determining whether the transmitting station has a capability to implement a secure block acknowledgment mechanism while setting up the block acknowledgement session;
after setting up the block acknowledgement session with the transmitting station, receiving an information unit during the block acknowledgment session with the transmitting station, the information unit including information indicative of a request for the communication device to adjust the receiving window;
determining whether the received information unit is encrypted;
adjusting the receiving window if the received information unit is encrypted; and
not adjusting the receiving window if (i) the received information unit is not encrypted, and (ii) the received information unit was expected to be encrypted.
